Farcaster, a decentralized social network built on Ethereum, is reshaping online communities by emphasizing user ownership and interoperability. Central to its ecosystem are mini apps—compact, web-based applications that integrate seamlessly with Farcaster’s infrastructure to enhance user engagement. Among these, Noice stands out as an innovative mini app that turns social interactions like likes, recasts, and comments into economic transactions. Accessible at farcaster.xyz/noiceapp, Noice is redefining how users and creators monetize attention in a decentralized social landscape. This article explores Noice’s functionality, its impact on the Farcaster community, and its role in the future of social media.

